The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Water tips from UK
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Water tips from UK
                            
	Environmental scientists from Queens University Belfast are coming to Calcutta on November 19 for a four-day visit to set up the Eastern India Water Research Institute.        
	The institute will be located at the Bengal Engineering and Science University (Besu), in Shibpur.        
	The new institute will carry out research in collaboration with Queens University, confirmed B.N. Dutta, the dean in-charge of sponsored research and institute-industry collaboration at Shibpur.        
	The scientists will not only aim to control arsenic levels in drinking water, but also develop better ways of tackling flooding in Calcutta.                                                                                                                                                                         
